ChangeHistory.Change: Increased Incharge CP line disconnect time
removed AC disconnect when DC is an option. Removed DC connect when AC is an option.
decreased timeout of DC test step from 100sec to 60sec
removed availability test step. Does not work appropriately with incharge.
Moved PLC Stop with delay before charger stop
remove BADDC from the DC Stop for OCPP comm
swopped back the stop. Inchar first PLC Second.
change timeout from 20 sec to 25 sec for the Ford
Increased Pass Window for V,I from the Incharge
raise cp connection chk from 5v to 6v
changed voltagerange tests to modbusvalidatevoltagerange tests per I/O board removal and ADAM modbus addition
added data reporting for voltage range
adjusted AC CP Line limits from 9000 to 9500 and lower 2000 to 4000
Fixed option mask for DC CP line, the test step would only run if DC and not AC
Moved tags from Test Data Reporting section to Test Data Display
Changed current low limit to 2 am AC
Removed Delay and Moved the CP_line Chk Before Start PLC
increased upper voltage limit DC Charging to 1000v for Type 3 Charging
Added Test for Vehicle shut down of charge session.
Added NOOP back to CP check
Added Check for estop on in the cable check group to abort program
Added check for Estop to all groups Cable ckeck, ac charge test and dc charge test
decrease Timeout from 3 min to 90 sec
Added "AC" and "DC" back to the prompt labels for seperate cables
Changed the Fault Id for AC Charge Current/Voltage out of range from 51779 to 51782
added manual charge time of 1 hr
